        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Temperatures sometimes rise or fall suddenly. For example, </p><p>Montana holds the United States record for the fastest rise in temperature over a 24-hour period. In 23 hours, the temperature changed from –54˚F to 49˚F in the town of Loma.</p><p><strong>January 14, 1972: 9 am –54˚F   →   January 15, 1972: 8 am 49˚F</strong></p><p>Montana also holds the world record for the fastest fall. Browning, MT, saw temperatures drop from 44°F to –56°F, in less than 24 hours.</p><p><strong>January 23, 1916: 9 am 44˚F  →   January 24, 1916: 8 am –56˚F</strong></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "2L8U7th3UCf7eAl_",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>How many degrees did the temperature rise in Loma, Montana? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
